						<summary>

						<p>Archaeological Range office: Two fragments found near the cistern close to the king's Audience hall in the ruins at Hampi. </p>						

						<p>10th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This fragmentary record in characters of about 10th century A.D. contains verses in praise of Jainamunis Guṇachandramuni, Indranandimuni and probably their disciple a lady who had obtained Sanyāsa had become a <hi rend="italic">‘Kaṅti’</hi> [a Jaina lady ascetic].</p>						

						</summary>
